<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Is Smartlead really better than Instantly for deliverability?</h3>
<p>Based on G2 reviews and Reddit threads, Smartlead's warmup customization is slightly more granular than Instantly's. However, deliverability depends more on your domain setup, sending volume, and email content than on the tool itself. Both tools offer competitive deliverability features. The main reason to switch is if you are experiencing specific deliverability issues with Instantly that you believe are platform-related.</p>

<h3>Can Apollo replace both Instantly and my data provider?</h3>
<p>Yes, for teams sending under 1,000 emails per week. Apollo combines a 275M+ contact database with email sequencing, so you can find leads and email them from one platform. However, Apollo's sending limits are lower than Instantly's, and it lacks unlimited mailbox support. If you send 5,000+ emails per week, you still need a dedicated sending tool.</p>

<h3>What is the cheapest Instantly alternative that actually works?</h3>
<p>Woodpecker ($20/mo) is the cheapest. Mailshake ($25/mo) is the best balance of price and features. Smartlead ($39/mo) is the closest feature match to Instantly. For most teams, Smartlead at $39/mo is the best value if you need Instantly-level features at a comparable price.</p>

